@NODE "GM_TEXTEDITOR_ARexxCmd" "texteditor.gadget/GM_TEXTEDITOR_ARexxCmd"
@{b}

    NAME@{ub}
        @{"GM_TEXTEDITOR_ARexxCmd" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/texteditor.h/File" 70}@{b}

    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        @{"DoGadgetMethod" LINK "GM_TEXTEDITOR_ExportBlock"}(obj, win, req, @{"GM_TEXTEDITOR_ARexxCmd" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/texteditor.h/File" 70}, @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}, @{"STRPTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 67} command);@{b}

    FUNCTION@{ub}
        If the user spends much of his time in the TextEditor gadget, then he
        may want to have the gadgets functions integrated in the programs
        arexx command set.
        This can easily be done with this method, simply call it with the
        command that the user has executed. If the method returns something
        else than @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}, then the command has been used by the gadget. If it
        does return @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}, then you should parse the command yourself.

        This method can also be used by you, to communicate with the gadget.

        The following commands are currently supported:

           CLEAR
           CUT
           COPY
           PASTE
           ERASE
           GOTOLINE       Template: /N/A
           GOTOCOLUMN     Template: /N/A
           CURSOR         Template: Up/S,Down/S,Left/S,Right/S
           LINE           Template: /N/A
           COLUMN         Template: /N/A
           NEXT           Template: Word/S,Sentence/S,Paragraph/S,Page/S
           PREVIOUS       Template: Word/S,Sentence/S,Paragraph/S,Page/S
           POSITION       Template: SOF/S,EOF/S,SOL/S,EOL/S,SOW/S,EOW/S,SOV/S,EOV/S
           SETBOOKMARK    Template: /N/A
           GOTOBOOKMARK   Template: /N/A
           @{"TEXT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 92}           Template: /F
           UNDO
           REDO
           GETLINE
           GETCURSOR      Template: Line/S,Column/S
           MARK           Template: On/S,Off/S
           DELETE
           BACKSPACE@{b}

    RESULT@{ub}
        The method will return @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98} if it couldn't use the command.
        It will return @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95} if it did use the command, but the command didn't
        give a result. It will return a pointer (@{"STRPTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 67}) when the command
        gives a result, you should return this pointer to the user
        (CreateArgString() it, and set it as the result, in the rexx message),
        you must free the result yourself with @{"FreeVec()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/exec/FreeVec"}

@ENDNODE
